Popstar Madonna visited Kenya on Sunday. She was in Baringo county. Taking to Twitter, she said, The popstar is famous for hits including 'like a prayer' and 'la isla bonita' having had a career spanning over three decades. Madonna was earlier in the month in Malawi. The US singer has six children, four of whom she adopted from Malawi. According to the BBC, Madonna has reportedly had a fractious relationship with authorities from the south-east African nation. In 2013, Malawi accused Madonna of "bullying state officials", exaggerating her contribution to the country and demanding VIP treatment. Madonna's manager accused Malawi's government of having a "grudge" against the singer's charity, Raising Malawi, which she founded in 2006, the same year she adopted David.